<h3>Source archive</h3>
You can download the latest source archive from
<a href=http://tamacom.com/global/global-4.2.tar.gz>global-4.2.tar.gz</a>.
<p>
You can also download it from GNU ftp site. See
<a href=http://www.gnu.org/order/ftp.html>GNU ftp list</a>.

<h3>CVS repository</h3>
You can browse the GLOBAL CVS repository via the
<a href=http://subversions.gnu.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb/global/>CVSweb interface</a>.
<p>
You can also use the <a href=http://www.gnu.org/software/cvs/cvs.html>
CVS utility</a> to obtain anonymous read-only access.
The module name is <strong>global</strong>.
<p>
You can get and build CVS version of GLOBAL like this:
<br>(You need automake and autoconf installed in your machine.
<br>Hit return when prompted for the login password.)
<p>
<pre>
% cvs -d:pserver:anoncvs@subversions.gnu.org:/cvsroot login
(Logging in to anoncvs@subversions.gnu.org)
CVS password: [RET]
% cvs -d:pserver:anoncvs@subversions.gnu.org:/cvsroot co global
% cd global
% sh reconf.sh 
% ./configure
% make
</pre>
Currently, following tags are available:
